Implementation plan for #752:

1. Add getFailureDetails(revision) to BaseStatusProvider with a default
   empty implementation so subclasses can override it.

2. Update waitForTheBuildToSucceed() to call getFailureDetails() and log
   each line at error level before throwing, so details appear in
   non-debug output.

3. In GitHubStatusProvider, cache the three API responses (commit status,
   check suites, check runs) as instance fields during getRevisionStatus().
   Override getFailureDetails() to iterate the cached data and collect:
   - Failed legacy commit statuses (context, state, target_url)
   - Failed check runs (name, conclusion, html_url)
   - A "See all checks" link to the GitHub commit page

4. Add unit tests covering: empty cache, failed legacy statuses, failed
   check runs, mixed failures, missing URLs, and the link footer.
